<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101777103652766></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101777103652766><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=15&mid=101777103652766>RE: I may be wrong...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=15&mid=101777103652766#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=155204><span id= >Chakshais</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 2nd 1:14 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is an Alternate Advancement skill that allows you to force your pet to hold aggression.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is one of the class skills available at level 59 when you have 6 points in General skills and 12 points in the Archetype skills.  So it will take quite a bit of work to get to that point.  Dungeon hunting with a Beastlord is no different than with any other class that has a pet.  Grouping is recommended however since Beastlords don't have the ability to Root or Snare runners.  That's where the problem with trains or excessive adds might come in.  To make sure your pet doesn't wander, which has been known to happen, make sure that when your group has come to the spot you're going to pull to that you park your pet with the &quot; /pet guard here &quot; command.  If you lose your pet in a dangerous area you can either cast Summon Companion (lvl 39) or destroy your warder by left clicking the icon and resummon another one.  If you see &quot;Taunting Attacker, Master&quot; but don't know where your warder is, then camping might be the best idea to lose aggro.  Otherwise your warder will likely be killed, followed shortly by you and your group due to the massive train she might have brought.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Apr  2 23:55:54 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
